History can be seen in time series energy graphs.
The effect of the 1970s oil crises can be seen in Figure~\ref{fig:EnergyPerPersonGraph}.
Per-capita primary energy consumption rose substantially from 1800 to 1970
with the adoption of fossil fuels worldwide.
Since the oil crises, efficiency and substitution 
have slowed the growth of per-capita energy primary consumption. 
China's entrance into the World Trade Organization in late 2001 led
to a noticeable rise in per-capita energy consumption.

