we form a term for the primary energy intensity of the world economy
as the example for resource intensity of the economy ($R$).
The energy intensity of the economy is formed
by dividing primary energy consumption ($E_p$) 
by world GDP,
i.e.\ dividing Figure~\ref{fig:PrimaryEnergyGraph} 
by Figure~\ref{fig:GDPGraph-Nordhaus}.
The result is Figure~\ref{fig:EnergyIntensityGraph-Nordhaus}.

