\section*{Questions}\index{questions}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

\begin{questions}

  \item Is the strong sustainability criterion appropriate?
        Or is it too severe for modern life today?
        Justify your answer.
  
  \item Is the Graedel and Allenby sustainability criterion a good criterion?
        What is the basis for your judgement?
      
  \item **** Finite vs.\ increasing resources. Mineral vs.\ labor. ****
  
  \item Maximum sustainable yield. If we harvest less than this we're ``leaving
        money on the table'' and our efficiency metrics are less good. How
        do we decide how much to take? Fish, e.g.
  
  \item Critique/reflect on the statement ``money is a lien on energy.''
  
  \item Some aquifers are ``fossil water.'' Research this statement. 
        Is using any such resource sustainable? What are the moral and
        ethical implications of leaving a valuable and usable resource \emph{unused}?

\end{questions}


